                detailedExample: 'Full opening example — Profitability case:\n\nInterviewer: "Our client is a supermarket chain. Their profits have dropped 15% in the past year. What\'s going on?"\n\nCandidate opening:\n"Let me make sure I understood correctly: we have a supermarket chain whose profits dropped 15% last year, and our goal is to identify the root cause and recommend actions. [Pause] Before I structure my approach, two quick questions: Is this profit drop happening across all stores or specific regions? And are we looking at operating profit or net profit?\n\n[Interviewer answers: all stores, operating profit]\n\nThank you. Give me 60 seconds to structure my approach.\n\n[Writes on paper]\n\nI\'d like to approach this in two areas: first the revenue side — price, volume, and mix — and second the cost side — fixed and variable costs. Within each I\'ll identify where the 15% drop is coming from before recommending actions. Does this structure make sense?"\n\nTotal: under 90 seconds. Clear, structured, confident.',
